ἓ 41. atque: according to the rules laid down by Madv. in his note to Fin. iv 20, 56 saeptum and munitum should here be taken closely together as forming the third phrase in the series, as according to him Cic. never in an enumeration of three or more terms puts a copula between the last two if they form independent terms in the series.
